An Ado-Ekiti Chief Magistrates’ Court, on Wednesday, remanded a 65-year-old man, Ezekiel Adewale, in correctional custody for allegedly raping an 11-year-old girl. The Chief Magistrate, Mr Abdulhamid Lawal, who did not take the plea of Adewale, ordered that the case file be sent to the Director of Public Prosecutions (DPP) for advice. Adewale then adjourned the case till Dec.18 for mention. ALSO READ: Police, declaring Nnamdi Kanu’s lawyer wanted, a plot to kill actualization ― IPOB Invest in girl-child education, encourage women… Police, declaring Nnamdi Kanu’s lawyer wanted, a plot… Abdulrazaq challenges Kwara cabinet members on task ahead IPOB: Nnamdi Kanu’s lawyer, Ejiofor speaks from hiding, says… The defendant, whose address was not provided, is facing a charge of rape. Earlier, the Prosecutor, Insp. Caleb Leranmo told the court that the defendant committed the offence on Nov 30 at Efon-Alaaye Ekiti. Leranmo said that the defendant lured the girl to his house with money and defiled her. He said that the girl told the police that the defendant had defiled her on three occasions. According to the prosecutor, the offence contravenes Section 31(2) of the Child Right Law of Ekiti, 2012. SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE
